    "body": "Because JSON doesn't take order into account, sort should be an array, not an object.\n\nFor instance:\n    sort : {\n        postDate : {reverse : true},\n        user : { },\n        score : { }\n    }\n\nis the equivalent of:\n\n```\nsort : {\n    score : { }\n    user : { },\n    postDate : {reverse : true},\n}\n```\n\nInstead, perhaps this syntax:\n\n```\nsort : [\n    \"score\",\n    \"user\",\n    { \"postDate\": { \"reverse\": true}} \n]\n```\n\nclint\n", 
